name: Sherrilyn Ifill
tweet: So much talk about ‚ÄúAmerican values.‚ÄùYou know one of the unique, verifiable American values? Your ‚Äúblood‚Äù heritage is supposed to be irrelevant to your status as an American. When this country has departed from that (thru racist immigration laws)it was a subversion of that value.

name: Sherrilyn Ifill
tweet: ...or claim to Americanness or citizenship. Media please STOP making it as thought this racist, ignorant and uninformed ‚ÄúAnglo-Saxon heritage‚Äù mvmt is part of any legitimate debate about who is American and who is not.

name: Sherrilyn Ifill
tweet: This country chose birthright citizenship (jus solis)& not the (common in Europe) ‚Äúblood‚Äù (jus sanguiness) conception of citizenship in 1868, precisely to secure the legitimacy of citizenship Black ppl here. Yr claim to ‚ÄúAnglo-Saxon‚Äù heritage does not increase your legitimacy...

tweet: A cable news host just said ‚Äúthere‚Äôs a difference of opinion right now about who is really American‚Äù and I feel like I‚Äôm going to lose it. tweet: We must break the regime of impunity that protects law enforcement ofcrs from consequences. Learn more about the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act  https://t.co/k4sN6Gloif And call your Senator and demand its passage: 202-224-3121.

name: Sherrilyn Ifill
tweet: And ofcrs will know that even if the local prosecutor or grand jury won‚Äôt charge or indict, or local jury won‚Äôt convict they‚Äôll face sure federal prosecution. They‚Äôll know they‚Äôll have to stand trial in civil ct. They‚Äôll know they‚Äôll never work in policing again.

name: Sherrilyn Ifill
tweet: To be clear, the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act won‚Äôt end all brutal policing. But it is designed to remove the critical legal barriers that block the ability to hold law enforcement ofcrs accountable for the kind of monstrous conduct you see in this video.

name: Sherrilyn Ifill
tweet: Let‚Äôs say these ofcrs are fired now that this video has been released. Should they be permitted to join the force of another law enforcement agency in another town? No. That‚Äôs why the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act would create a national police misconduct database.

name: Sherrilyn Ifill
tweet: Can the ofcrs be sued civilly for damages? Sure.Then they‚Äôll raise the defense of qualified immunity. That‚Äôs why the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act would end qualified immunity for law enforcement ofcrs, which would give families the chance to hold these ofcrs accountable.

name: Sherrilyn Ifill
tweet: Can the feds try the ofcrs? They should certainly try. But the fed crim statute (section 242) has a high standard. That‚Äôs why the George Floyd Justice in Policing Act would change the standard of illegal ofcr conduct from ‚Äúwillfulness‚Äù to ‚Äúrecklessness.‚Äù

tweet: Violent crimes are not solved by police acting on their own - no matter what you see on TV. It requires the engagement of community members working w public safety ofcrs they trust. Trust is at an all-time low. That‚Äôs why police lying, misconduct & brutality drives up crime.

tweet: And I will keep saying, crime rises when 1) the root causes of violence are not addressed (poverty, joblessness, trauma & abuse) and 2) when violent crimes are not solved. Look at the abysmal clearance rate for murder in most cities.
